TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.


$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$m = random(2,8,2);
$k = random(1,7,2);

$ans = "($k - e^x)/$m";

BEGIN_TEXT
Question 20:
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
Find the inverse function (if it exists) of $SPACE \( f(x) = \ln{($k - $m x)} \) .  If the function is not invertible, enter $BBOLD NONE $EBOLD . 
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
\( f^{-1}(x) = \) \{ ans_rule(30) \} 
$BR
(notice in this problem the independent variable in the inverse is $BITALIC x${EITALIC})
$BR

END_TEXT

ANS(fun_cmp( $ans, vars=>'x' ) );

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR 
Start with our property of inverse functions \( f \left( f^{-1}(x) \right) = x \), and substitute \( y \) for \( f^{-1}(x) \) to get \( f(y)=x \). Now, using the formula for \( f \) we get \( \displaystyle f(y) = \ln{($k - $m y)} =x \)
and solving for \( y \) yields
$BR $SPACE $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ x = f(y) \)
$BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ x = \ln{($k-$m y)} \)
$BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ e^x = e^{(\ln{ ($k-$m y)}} \)
$BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ e^x = $k-$m y \)
$BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ $m y = $k - e^x \)
$BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ y = \frac{$k - e^x}{$m} \).
$BR $SPACE $BR
Thus \( y=f^{-1}(x) = \displaystyle \frac{$k - e^x}{$m} \).
$BR
END_SOLUTION

